===Etymology===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} – a footprint, originally meaning "toe". The derivative [[趾]] refers to the original meaning. Compare {{m|mul|手||hand|sc=Hani}}. Note that in oracle script, composed of 3 toes and a sole.

Compare to [[夊]], [[夂]], which have similar shape in oracle script, but pointing down (toe pointing right), and [[𡕒]] (as in right side of [[舛]], roughly [[ヰ]], toe pointing left), hence different evolution.

